Note that, for $x \geq i$, $\binom{x}{i}$ is increasing as a function of $x$, and if $y \geq i + \frac{3}{2}\alpha$, then
\begin{align*}
\binom{y}{i} 
&= \prod_{j=0}^{i-1} \frac{y-j}{i-j} 
\geq \prod_{j=0}^{i-1} \bigg(1 + \frac{3\alpha/2}{i-j}\bigg) \geq \exp\bigg( \left(\frac{3}{2}+o(1)\right)  \alpha \sum_{j=0}^{i-\log i}\frac{1}{i-j}\bigg)\\ 
&\geq \exp\left( \left(\frac{3}{2}+o(1)\right)\alpha \log i \right) = \Omega\left(d^{(3/2+o(1))\alpha}\right),
\end{align*}
using the fact that $1+z \geq \e^{(1+o(1))z}$ for $z = o(1)$ and that $\sum_{j=0}^{i-\log i}\frac{1}{i-j} = (1+o(1)) \log i$. 
In particular, it follows that $x \leq i + \frac{3}{2}\alpha$ and, hence,
\[
\frac{i}{3\alpha}\binom{x}{i} = \frac{x-i+1}{3\alpha}\binom{x}{i-1}\le \binom{x}{i-1}.\qedhere
\]

